Note:
TRIE - Prefix Tree Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements a 256-ary trie keyed by byte strings (Strings are
null-terminated byte sequences in the bootstrap runtime). Each node
holds a value slot and a 256-entry children array (one per possible
byte). The trie supports prefix-based search and is the substrate for
autocomplete, IP routing prefix dispatch, and dictionary lookups.

Node structure (8 + 8 + 8 + 256 * 8 = 2072 bytes):
  offset 0:    has_value flag (8 bytes)
  offset 8:    value (8 bytes; only meaningful when has_value == 1)
  offset 16:   child_count (8 bytes; bookkeeping for fast empty check)
  offset 24+:  children array (256 * 8 = 2048 bytes)

Trie header (16 bytes):
  offset 0: root pointer
  offset 8: entry_count (8 bytes; total number of terminated keys)
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let TRIE_ALPHABET_SIZE be 256
Let TRIE_NODE_SIZE be 2072
Let TRIE_HEADER_SIZE be 16
Let TRIE_CHILDREN_OFFSET be 24

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Address of the child slot for byte 'b' in a node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
addr = node + 24 + b * 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-validated byte (0..255).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_child_addr" takes node as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return node plus (TRIE_CHILDREN_OFFSET plus (b multiplied by 8))
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a new trie node. Layout.allocate zero-fills so all child slots
are null, has_value = 0, child_count = 0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
2072-byte allocation; zero-init by allocator.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 2072 bytes per node.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_node_create" returns Integer:
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with TRIE_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 16, 0
    Note: Children are zero-initialized by the allocator.
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TREE CONSTRUCTION / DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Create an empty trie with a single root node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate header, allocate root, link, entry_count = 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_create" returns Integer:
    Let trie be proc allocate from Layout with TRIE_HEADER_SIZE
    If trie is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc trie_node_create
    If root is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with trie
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with trie, 0, root
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with trie, 8, 0
    Return trie
End Process

@Reasoning
Free every node iteratively using a stack of node pointers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Maintain a dynamic stack buffer of pointers. Pop each node, push every
non-null child, free the popped node. Postorder is implicit because
children are pushed before the parent is freed but freeing only
happens after we've pushed all children.

Implementation detail: nodes with no children are freed first because
they're at the top of the stack when popped without further pushes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(N) in node count. Space: O(N) in the worst case (the stack can
contain many siblings simultaneously).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_destroy" takes trie as Integer returns Integer:
    If trie is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with trie, 0
    Let cap be 64
    Let buf_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be 0
    If root is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, root
        Set sp to 1
    End If
    While sp is greater than 0:
        Set sp to sp minus 1
        Let off be sp multiplied by 8
        Let node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf, off
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than TRIE_ALPHABET_SIZE:
            Let c_addr be proc trie_child_addr with node, i
            Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
            If child is not equal to 0:
                Let need be sp plus 1
                If need is greater than cap:
                    Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
                    Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
                    Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
                    If new_buf is equal to 0:
                        proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
                    proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
                    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                    Set buf to new_buf
                    Set cap to new_cap
                End If
                Let s_off be sp multiplied by 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, s_off, child
                Set sp to sp plus 1
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc deallocate from Layout with node
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
    proc deallocate from Layout with trie
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Number of complete-key entries in the trie.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read entry_count at offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_size" takes trie as Integer returns Integer:
    If trie is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with trie, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STRING LENGTH HELPER (null-terminated)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Local string-length helper to avoid bringing in the text module for
this single use. Walks until a null byte.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Loop until *(ptr + i) == 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must supply a null-terminated string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_strlen" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, i
        If byte is equal to 0:
            Return i
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return i
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INSERT / LOOKUP / DELETE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Insert key (null-terminated String) with associated value. If the key
already exists, overwrite the value rather than incrementing the count.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Walk down from root, byte by byte. At each byte, if the child slot
   is empty, allocate a fresh node and link it. Bump child_count of
   the parent when a new slot is filled.
2) After consuming all bytes, mark the terminal node has_value = 1
   and set value. If it was newly marked, increment entry_count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k) where k is key length. Space: O(k) in the worst case (each
byte may allocate one new node).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_insert" takes trie as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If trie is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with trie, 0
    Let i be 0
    Let klen be proc trie_strlen with key
    While i is less than klen:
        Let byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with key, i
        Let c_addr be proc trie_child_addr with cur, byte
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
        If child is equal to 0:
            Set child to proc trie_node_create
            If child is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0, child
            Let cc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 16, cc plus 1
        End If
        Set cur to child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let had be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 0, 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 8, value
    If had is equal to 0:
        Let ec be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with trie, 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with trie, 8, ec plus 1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Lookup value for key. Returns value if present, 0 if absent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk down child[byte] for each byte; if a child is null partway, return
0. After consuming all bytes, return value if has_value == 1, else 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_lookup" takes trie as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If trie is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with trie, 0
    Let i be 0
    Let klen be proc trie_strlen with key
    While i is less than klen:
        Let byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with key, i
        Let c_addr be proc trie_child_addr with cur, byte
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
        If child is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set cur to child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let has_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
    If has_value is equal to 1:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Contains predicate (distinguishes "present with value 0" from "absent").
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same descent as lookup but returns 1 on has_value match.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_contains" takes trie as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If trie is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with trie, 0
    Let i be 0
    Let klen be proc trie_strlen with key
    While i is less than klen:
        Let byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with key, i
        Let c_addr be proc trie_child_addr with cur, byte
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
        If child is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set cur to child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let has_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
    Return has_value
End Process

@Reasoning
Find the node at which a given prefix ends; returns 0 if any byte of
the prefix is missing. Used as the entry point for prefix enumeration.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk down child[byte] for each prefix byte.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_prefix_node" takes trie as Integer, prefix as Integer returns Integer:
    If trie is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If prefix is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with trie, 0
    Let i be 0
    Let plen be proc trie_strlen with prefix
    While i is less than plen:
        Let byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with prefix, i
        Let c_addr be proc trie_child_addr with cur, byte
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
        If child is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set cur to child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return cur
End Process

@Reasoning
Count entries with the given prefix. Walks the subtree rooted at the
prefix node and counts has_value == 1 along the way.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Find subtree root via trie_prefix_node.
2) Walk the subtree iteratively using a node stack.
3) Each node contributes 1 to the count if has_value == 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(M) where M is the number of nodes in the prefix subtree.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_prefix_count" takes trie as Integer, prefix as Integer returns Integer:
    Let sub_root be proc trie_prefix_node with trie, prefix
    If sub_root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be 64
    Let buf_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, sub_root
    Set sp to 1
    Let count be 0
    While sp is greater than 0:
        Set sp to sp minus 1
        Let off be sp multiplied by 8
        Let node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf, off
        Let has_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
        If has_value is equal to 1:
            Set count to count plus 1
        End If
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than TRIE_ALPHABET_SIZE:
            Let c_addr be proc trie_child_addr with node, i
            Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c_addr, 0
            If child is not equal to 0:
                Let need be sp plus 1
                If need is greater than cap:
                    Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
                    Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
                    Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
                    If new_buf is equal to 0:
                        proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                        Return count
                    End If
                    Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
                    proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
                    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                    Set buf to new_buf
                    Set cap to new_cap
                End If
                Let s_off be sp multiplied by 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, s_off, child
                Set sp to sp plus 1
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
    Return count
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: does any entry with this prefix exist?
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Calls trie_prefix_node; returns 1 if non-null and the subtree contains
at least one has_value node. Uses prefix_count > 0 for the second
condition because the prefix node itself might not be terminal.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k + M).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "trie_has_prefix" takes trie as Integer, prefix as Integer returns Integer:
    Let n be proc trie_prefix_node with trie, prefix
    If n is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let c be proc trie_prefix_count with trie, prefix
    If c is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process
